cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper proposes a novel approach for cost-adjustable inference in convolutional networks (CNNs) and validates its effectiveness through extensive experiments on image classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the regularization boost provided by sharing network parameters across different instances, which suggests that it may also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the stochastic downsampling technique used in the proposed approach involves randomization, which is a common technique in the field of neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely category. Finally, the paper deals with image classification, which is a common task in natural language processing, suggesting that it may also belong to the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
